##  Reflection

This task reinforced the importance of formal, documented decisions in GRC work. A signed ATO isn't just symbolic â€” it's a **binding acceptance of residual risk**.

As a system owner or security leader, receiving that ATO is a moment of pride â€” but also responsibility. From here forward, we must **maintain continuous compliance**, address any outstanding POA&M items, and prepare for eventual re-authorization.

Ask yourself:
